rows.title: JRPG Traitor
rows.titleText:
Welcome to JRPG Traitor Interactive!

Original by JRPG
Static: https://imgur.com/a/xy9tgBB
Interactive by Pasadena
Version: v1.0

Notes:
- The latter half of the points are only for debug purposes
- Powers that require "X amount of tokens spent", "X number of elements", etc have no requirements, so it's up to you to count them
- There is no rule enforcing how many mentors and apprentices you can have, so keep to one at a time (post-betrayal can have one so long as your mentor/apprentice didn't follow you) unless you have the relevant perks

rows.title: Powerful
rows.titleText: Allocate your 15 extra tokens. Make sure to count properly.

rows.title: Hatred
rows.titleText: What brings you hatred? Choose one.

objects.title: Grounded Hatred
objects.text: Your hatred is for an individual or institution, something you can put down.

objects.title: Ideal Hatred
objects.text: Your hatred is for society and its rules, which have done you terrible harm.

objects.title: Existential Hatred
objects.text: Your hatred is for an unavoidable part of the mortal condition.

rows.title: Loss
rows.titleText: What is your new purpose? Choose one.

objects.title: Never Again
objects.text: You have found a replacement, and all that you do is solely to protect it from harm.

objects.title: No One Else
objects.text: What you lost is gone, but you’ll protect others from suffering as you have.

objects.title: They Will Pay
objects.text: What you lost has become a mere excuse to enact your vengeance.

rows.title: Duty
rows.titleText: Who is your master?

rows.title: Love
rows.titleText: How does love affect your reason? Choose one.

objects.title: Unquestionable Loyalty
objects.text: Your love has aligned themselves against the Heroes, and thus, so have you.

objects.title: Pragmatic Reasoning
objects.text: After a cold analysis, the Overlord’s victory is what’s best for your love.

objects.title: At All Costs
objects.text: Your love is in danger, and you will do whatever it takes to save them.

rows.title: Something Else
rows.titleText: What is your reason? Choose one.

objects.title: Mastered
objects.text: You are being controlled, threatened, deceived, or otherwise coerced.

objects.title: Knowledge
objects.text: You are doing it for the sake of knowledge.

objects.title: Mentality
objects.text: It is intrinsic, such as a split personality, or being pure evil.

rows.title: Harsh Training
rows.titleText: What did you train? Choose one.

objects.title: Body
objects.text: What you trained was your body, like the beastmen warriors of old.

objects.title: Mind
objects.text: Your mind was refined to be the match of any mage.

objects.title: Soul
objects.text: You lived the old ways, becoming both clever and cruel.

rows.title: Blood Relation
rows.titleText: Which type of token does the character grant the most? If there are more than one at the highest, select any. Choose one.

rows.title: Fortuitous Rescue
rows.titleText: How did you save your Innocent? Choose one.

objects.title: Valiantly
objects.text: You did it by strength of arms, like a gallant knight.

objects.title: Miraculously
objects.text: Like a wizard from a children’s tale, your magic made their problems disappear.

objects.title: Trickily
objects.text: With guile and a bit of cold blood, you made them come out unscathed.

rows.title: Unfortunate Meeting
rows.titleText: How did you gain your villainous acquaintance? Choose one.

objects.title: Mercenary
objects.text: They needed muscle, and you gave them what they asked for.

objects.title: Dark Arts
objects.text: You had to turn your brilliance to darker pursuits.

objects.title: Overconfidence
objects.text: They underestimated you and came out as the loser of their game.

rows.title: Fireside Chat
rows.titleText: What type of token does the character grant the most? If there are more than one at the highest, select any. Choose one.

rows.title: A Secret Admirer
rows.titleText: Why do they admire you?

objects.title: Strength
objects.text: They admire you for your strength of both body and character.

objects.title: Intelligence
objects.text: They praise your sharp mind and contributions to magic.

objects.title: Paragon
objects.text: They call you a source of inspiration and aspire to imitate you.

rows.title: Bad Friend
rows.titleText: Why is the villain interested in you?

objects.title: Strength
objects.text: They are very interested in your strength.

objects.title: Intelligence
objects.text: They need someone intelligent for reasons they won’t disclose.

objects.title: Enlightenment
objects.text: They see something worth bringing into the light within you.

rows.title: Old Soldier's End
rows.titleText:
Note: Only characters with the Mentor trait can be selected.

Are you responsible for the old mentor’s death?

objects.title: No
objects.text: You played no part in their death.

objects.title: Somewhat
objects.text: It was planned by you, at least in part.

objects.title: Yes
objects.text: You, undetected, directly participated in their demise.

rows.title: Unexpected Death
rows.titleText: How do you relate to the party member’s death?

objects.title: Last Words
objects.text: It was you who relayed their last words to the rest of the party.

objects.title: Calming Presence
objects.text: You calmed down the rest of the party after the event.

objects.title: Sinister Plot
objects.text: You had a hand in their death, someway or another.

rows.title: Evil's Might
rows.titleText: How did you react to the attack?

objects.title: Bravely
objects.text: You were the last to flee, holding the enemy at bay by sheer force of will.

objects.title: Intelligently
objects.text: Your strategy ensured that everyone made it out safely.

objects.title: Cowardly
objects.text: You were the first to turn tail and flee.

rows.title: Evil Words, Evil Deeds
rows.titleText: If (and only if) the Overlord was already friendly with you, receive an extra token of your choice for this event.

rows.title: Rotten Apple
rows.titleText: How did you secure their loyalty?

objects.title: Loyalty
objects.text: They will follow you because of trust, loyalty, or love.

objects.title: Reason
objects.text: You convinced them with reason and proof.

objects.title: Coercion
objects.text: You forced, controlled, blackmails, or otherwise coerced them into it.

rows.title: Combat Tournament
rows.titleText: Choose only one:

objects.text:
===
If your opponent wasn’t someone you knew, choose only one, and ignore the last section.

If you knew them, skip to the next section.
===

===
If your opponent was someone you already knew, gain two extra tokens of your choice, and the friendship of the chosen character.

Only give yourself TWO tokens, no more.
===

rows.title: Three Dragons
rows.titleText: Which dragon did you face?

objects.title: Ageratina
objects.text: You fought against Ageratina, the Everblossoming, famed by her immortality.

objects.title: Orcus
objects.text: You defeated Orcus, who was turned into the Sixth’s greatest weapon.

objects.title: Albus
objects.text: You bested Albus, famed as the steed of Death.

rows.title: Twisted Connection
rows.titleText: Why are you and the character now friends?

objects.title: Hatred
objects.text: You bonded over your mutual hatred of your enemies.

objects.title: Drive
objects.text: You both shared the same determination to reach your goals.

objects.title: Desire
objects.text: You bonded over sharing the same dark desires, and the methods to indulge in them.

rows.title: What Goes Around…
rows.titleText: How do you react to being betrayed?

objects.title: Apathetic
objects.text: You are unbothered. It was a good attempt, but not good enough.

objects.title: Priorities
objects.text: You have bigger things to do, but you intend to flay the flesh off their bones someday.

objects.title: Revenge
objects.text: You made it your mission to find and kill them.

rows.title: Dark Love
rows.titleText: Why did they enter into the relationship?

objects.title: Power
objects.text: They love you for your strength, and what you can do for them.

objects.title: Dependence
objects.text: They need your guidance, being little more than lost sheep without you.

objects.title: Obsession
objects.text: They are unhealthily obsessed with you.

rows.title: In Control
rows.titleText: How has your relationship changed?

objects.title: Fear
objects.text: Your relationship is tempered by fear, for you are much stronger than they are.

objects.title: Manipulation
objects.text: You have managed to convince them that they enjoy being under you.

objects.title: No Competition
objects.text: No one loves them as much as you. You’ve made sure of that.

rows.title: Pitiful Child
rows.titleText: How will you treat your protege?

objects.title: Training
objects.text: You will make them strong. Strong enough to not need you.

objects.title: Succession
objects.text: You will pass unto them your knowledge so that it might not be lost.

objects.title: True Self
objects.text: You will ask them to remember you as you truly are.

rows.title: Sculptor
rows.titleText: What will you turn your apprentice into?

objects.title: A Tool
objects.text: A weapon of destruction, unthinking and lethal.

objects.title: A Test Subject
objects.text: A testbed for your wild and dangerous magical theories.

objects.title: A Paramour
objects.text: A perfect spouse, to suit your unique and demanding tastes.

rows.title: Unexpected Rescue
rows.titleText: Why did you save them?

objects.title: Lingering Affection
objects.text: You did it because you still hold some sort of affection towards them.

objects.title: Nothing Personal
objects.text: You did it for your benefit, or you were just following another’s orders.

objects.title: Only I Get To Kill Them
objects.text: You won’t let the Heroes perish at the hands of anyone but you.

rows.title: Bad Apple
rows.titleText: What are your mentor’s thoughts on you?

objects.title: Headstrong
objects.text: They’re headstrong and don’t see how protecting you is bad.

objects.title: Forgiveness
objects.text: They’re convinced you are worth forgiving for your sins.

objects.title: Charmed
objects.text: You’ve charmed them into loving you like their own flesh and blood.

rows.title: Crocodile Tears
rows.titleText: Why has the mentor decided to stay with you?

objects.title: No Return
objects.text: They have killed far too many to go back, even if they see through the facade.

objects.title: Knowledge
objects.text: With the things you know, it would be foolish to abandon you.

objects.title: Love Blinds
objects.text: They’re far too infatuated with you to realize the truth.

rows.title: A New Friend
rows.titleText:
Note: Hero characters cannot be explicitly chosen at this time. Be prepared to write down your decision.

Who did you unlock?

objects.title: Fighter
objects.text: The character was a Fighter.

objects.title: Innocent
objects.text: The character was an Innocent.

objects.title: Healer
objects.text: The character was a Healer.

objects.title: Mage
objects.text: The character was a Mage.

objects.title: Wanderer
objects.text: The character was a Wanderer.

objects.title: Villain
objects.text: The character was a Villain.

rows.title: Mentors
rows.titleText:
Each choice will take a Mentor point.

You will need to be a child or adolescent to take a mentor.

rows.title: Apprentices
rows.titleText:
Each choice will take an Apprentice point.

You will need to be an adult or an elder to take an apprentice.

rows.title: Friends
rows.titleText: Each choice will take a Friend point.

rows.title: Romances
rows.titleText:
Each choice will take a Romantic Interest point.

You will need to be compatible with your chosen character's sexual preference.

If they are a Hero, they must be apart of the party. If they are an Innocent or Villain, they must have been unlocked.

rows.title: The End
rows.titleText:
Thank you for playing!

This is just the initial release, and is bound to have some bugs or missing functionality. Feedback and suggestions are appreciated!

Don't worry if I've addressed it in the TODO section below, I'm already aware and am planning to fix it at some point.

If anyone wants to make a text version of this interactive, or wants to copy the flavor text, feel free to use this doc I made a while back (back in September 2022 when I was planning to make a text-based version before giving up lol), that has most of the images transcribed, save for Advanced Green Powers, Innocents, and Villains. The doc also has some commentary and thoughts by me on powers and stuff (though I never intended for it to be public lol).

Here is that doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vTAJ-P781Momysqcgb1-iibjqLG43x2avPGzk2fW_L1Gh7FQDQBVFI5R2VgIvFBYXZjqieJn8lQukCk/pub

objects.title: Credits
objects.text:
The original static CYOA was posted anonymously on the 4chan board /tg/, but is referred to as "JRPG" in the Allsync.

You can view it here: https://imgur.com/a/xy9tgBB

 I used the Allsync version of the CYOA for the highest quality.

The Allsync is here: https://cyoaarchive.com/main

And the link to the folder is: https://cyoa.allsync.com/s/owWor64yLTngDk3?path=%2FCYOA%20Creators%2C%20Authors%2FJRPG%27s%20CYOAs
